      "span_text": "Qualitative Study An Australian study, comprising in-depth interviews and diary-style data collection with 31 smokers and attempting quitters, investigated how the tobacco retail environment affected tobacco purchases or smoking after the implementation of POS display bans.  Thematic analysis of interviews suggested that a decrease of environmental smoking cues reduces temptation to smoke and contributes to lower smoking.",
